Trim and coarsely grate the @carrot{1} and @courgette{1/2}. Pop the veggies into a
#mixing bowl{} and add the @British beef mince{120%g}, @dried Italian herbs{1/2},
@tomato ketchup{1}, @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} and a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Use your hands to mix together well then shape the mixture into
four meatballs per person. Set aside on a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for
the pasta. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium
heat. When hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned, carefully turning
occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: You may have to do this in batches - don't overcrowd them.

When browned, remove to a plate.

> TIP: The meatballs won't be cooked all the way through - don't worry, we'll
> finish them off later!

Add the @spaghetti{250%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for
~{11%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}, return to the pan (off the heat) and
drizzle with @oil{drizzle} to stop it sticking. Meanwhile, return the now empty
frying pan to medium heat and add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(with onion and garlic),
@beef stock powder{1/2}, @tomato{2%medium}(chopped) and a pinch of
@sugar{pinch} if you have any. Stir, bring to the boil then reduce the heat and
simmer until thick and tomatoey, stirring occasionally, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the pasta and sauce cook, make the salad. Trim the @cucumber{1/2} then
quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Chop the tomato into
small pieces. Pop the cucumber and tomato in a large #bowl{} along with the
@balsamic vinegar{6%ml}, a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @pepper{pinch}. Toss together and set aside. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(stalks and all).

When the sauce is nice and thick, stir through half the parsley. Season to
taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Carefully return the meatballs to the pan and
bubble for ~{2-3%minutes}, until the meatballs are cooked through and piping
hot.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Divide the spaghetti between your plates and top with the meatballs and sauce.
Sprinkle on plenty of @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and sprinkle over
the remaining parsley. Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!